ECS: ELASTIC CONTAINER SERVICE.

ECS service is used to easily manage,update and deploy our containers.
ECS is a orchestration service available in aws.

Example: K8s,Docker Swarm,Mesos

Cluster: Group of ec2 servers
ECS-Agent: to maintain/keep the details of ec2 cluster,tasks and other resource utilization.
Task Definition: Blueprint of container example image url,port number,volumes and memory and cpu details.
Tasks: Task is nothing but running containers
Services: This will helps us to provide ASG to our tasks.

Replica services place and maintain a desired number of tasks across your cluster.
Daemon services place and maintain one copy of your task on each container instance. 

AWS Fargate is a technology that you can use with Amazon ECS to run containers without 
having to manage servers or clusters of Amazon EC2 instances.
